This paper discusses machine learning methods for text classification, which falls under the category of natural language processing (NLP). Therefore, cs.CL (Computation and Language) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also discusses the use of different algorithms and techniques, which suggests that it could also fall under cs.LG (Machine Learning). Additionally, the paper covers dimensionality reduction methods, which is a common technique in information retrieval (IR), making cs.IR another likely sub-category. The use of machine learning algorithms for text classification also falls under the category of artificial intelligence (AI), making cs.AI a possible sub-category. Finally, the paper discusses the application of text classification in real-world problems, which could also fall under computer vision (CV), making cs.CV a less likely but still possible sub-category.
